foundation / com.sap.cloud.mobile.foundation.cache / Cache / put

put

@Nullable abstract fun put(@NonNull key: K, @NonNull value: V, cost: Double): V?

Adds the value and the associated cost to the cache for the key. The behavior when the aggregate of costs exceeds the maximum cost during the execution of this method is implementation dependent.

Parameters

key - K: a non-null key of a cache entry

value - V: a non-null value to add

cost - Double: the cost associated with this entry. If the accumulated cost exceeds maximum cache cost, cache entry eviction may be triggered to free up memory space.

Return
V?: The previous value associated with the existed key, null if the entry did exist.

@Nullable abstract fun put(@NonNull key: K, @NonNull value: V): V?

Adds or updates a value associated with a key.

Parameters

key - K: a non-null key of a cache entry

value - V: a non-null value to add

Return
V?: The original value of an existing cache entry, or null if this is a new entry.
